1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
=Episode 11=

3
00:01:40,800 --> 00:01:46,000
(Luzhou No. 1 Women's Prison)

4
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,879
I want to go to Clear Water Bay.

5
00:03:28,360 --> 00:03:29,080
It's been five years.

6
00:03:30,199 --> 00:03:31,240
I kept thinking

7
00:03:32,479 --> 00:03:34,080
what's it like now?

8
00:03:35,639 --> 00:03:36,919
Now it's still completely barren.

9
00:03:39,840 --> 00:03:42,159
Chen Liyang showed me
the blueprints and said

10
00:03:43,159 --> 00:03:44,800
this would become an amusement park.

11
00:03:45,840 --> 00:03:47,319
It would be our new beginning.

12
00:03:50,039 --> 00:03:51,120
Then he died.

13
00:03:53,960 --> 00:03:55,400
Leaving nothing but a mess.

14
00:04:02,680 --> 00:04:03,960
I can't even remember clearly

15
00:04:04,840 --> 00:04:06,000
how Chen Liyang looked.

16
00:04:08,159 --> 00:04:08,840
Strange, isn't it?

17
00:04:11,479 --> 00:04:12,599
Human's memory

18
00:04:14,680 --> 00:04:15,599
is just absurd.

19
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:19,680
So many people and things
we should remember

20
00:04:20,000 --> 00:04:20,759
have become blurry.

21
00:04:21,920 --> 00:04:22,879
Things we shouldn't remember

22
00:04:24,759 --> 00:04:25,839
stay carved in the heart.

23
00:04:27,399 --> 00:04:28,920
They all say I owe Chen Liyang.

24
00:04:32,199 --> 00:04:32,959
Do I?

25
00:04:35,560 --> 00:04:36,439
It's all in the past.

26
00:04:39,959 --> 00:04:40,800
All in the past?

27
00:04:52,199 --> 00:04:54,000
From now on,
I decide how long it stays on.

28
00:04:54,160 --> 00:04:54,920
How long it stays off.

29
00:04:56,319 --> 00:04:56,839
I turn it on.

30
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:58,680
I turn it off.

31
00:05:01,639 --> 00:05:02,639
Everything here is ready.

32
00:05:03,279 --> 00:05:04,519
If you need anything else,

33
00:05:05,680 --> 00:05:06,439
just let me know.

34
00:05:15,720 --> 00:05:16,279
What Mr. Chen

35
00:05:17,240 --> 00:05:18,959
left in Unit 505 is money.

36
00:05:19,759 --> 00:05:20,519
There is 30 million.

37
00:05:21,720 --> 00:05:23,600
The new homeowner you mentioned before,

38
00:05:23,800 --> 00:05:24,720
Yu... what's his name?

39
00:05:25,199 --> 00:05:25,759
Yu Ming.

40
00:05:26,600 --> 00:05:27,879
Send me his number.

41
00:05:34,199 --> 00:05:35,519
Cut it to about this length.

42
00:05:36,439 --> 00:05:37,360
Trim the bangs,

43
00:05:37,439 --> 00:05:38,560
frame the face.

44
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:40,519
Then just dye it, alright?

45
00:05:43,240 --> 00:05:44,519
Hello. Welcome.

46
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,319
What can we do for you?

47
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:51,519
A whole new look.

48
00:06:46,199 --> 00:06:46,680
Who is this?

49
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:48,399
This is Li Jin.

50
00:06:49,399 --> 00:06:50,600
I'm Chen Zinuo's mother.

51
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:54,120
The money in Unit 505
is with you, right?

52
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,199
Let's meet and talk.

53
00:07:07,279 --> 00:07:08,319
Li Jin?

54
00:07:09,040 --> 00:07:10,199
Chen Zinuo's mother?

55
00:07:12,199 --> 00:07:13,160
Look.

56
00:07:13,160 --> 00:07:13,600
Is it her?

57
00:07:13,920 --> 00:07:15,600
What's the point of looking at that?

58
00:07:15,720 --> 00:07:16,759
I don't know her.

59
00:07:17,079 --> 00:07:19,199
Five-year sentence?

60
00:07:19,839 --> 00:07:20,920
It's not yet five years.

61
00:07:21,079 --> 00:07:21,959
Released early

62
00:07:22,079 --> 00:07:22,879
for good behavior.

63
00:07:22,959 --> 00:07:24,160
When you answered her call,

64
00:07:24,160 --> 00:07:25,199
did she sound

65
00:07:25,240 --> 00:07:25,879
normal?

66
00:07:26,319 --> 00:07:26,920
What mood?

67
00:07:27,199 --> 00:07:27,800
Very calm.

68
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:28,720
Very cold.

69
00:07:28,959 --> 00:07:31,399
Like a frozen lake.

70
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,759
That doesn't sound normal either.

71
00:07:32,839 --> 00:07:34,079
And Chen Zinuo isn't exactly normal.

72
00:07:34,199 --> 00:07:35,680
She say she'd rather
sleep on the streets

73
00:07:35,680 --> 00:07:36,399
than take the money.

74
00:07:36,480 --> 00:07:37,160
Said it was dirty.

75
00:07:37,319 --> 00:07:38,279
First the daughter,

76
00:07:38,279 --> 00:07:39,160
now the mother.

77
00:07:39,600 --> 00:07:41,279
Like mother,

78
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:43,079
like daughter.

79
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,319
That's her.

80
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:53,360
She's not here to play nice.

81
00:07:54,759 --> 00:07:55,759
Neither are we.

82
00:07:56,439 --> 00:07:57,600
Got a plan to deal with her?

83
00:07:58,600 --> 00:07:59,279
Just don't give it back.

84
00:08:01,199 --> 00:08:01,600
Right.

85
00:08:01,959 --> 00:08:02,720
Don't give it back.

86
00:08:14,480 --> 00:08:16,480
Keeping someone else's property
is illegal.

87
00:08:17,560 --> 00:08:18,600
Once I sue you,

88
00:08:19,279 --> 00:08:19,759
you,

89
00:08:20,759 --> 00:08:21,319
you two,

90
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,000
will have to return every cent,

91
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:25,360
pay court fees,

92
00:08:25,879 --> 00:08:27,399
and cover the late interest.

93
00:08:28,360 --> 00:08:29,199
30 million

94
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,600
is a huge amount.

95
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,159
You'll end up in jail.

96
00:08:34,720 --> 00:08:35,799
You can do

97
00:08:35,799 --> 00:08:36,960
whatever you want.

98
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,240
What about your parents?

99
00:08:39,120 --> 00:08:39,840
Your child?

100
00:08:40,799 --> 00:08:42,519
College applications?
Decent jobs? Still possible?

101
00:08:42,759 --> 00:08:43,679
So let me ask you

102
00:08:44,720 --> 00:08:46,000
how can you prove

103
00:08:46,320 --> 00:08:47,279
the money is yours?

104
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:49,879
Can you explain where did this money

105
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:51,200
come from?

106
00:08:51,519 --> 00:08:52,519
Can you explain that?

107
00:08:58,080 --> 00:08:58,679
A few thousand,

108
00:08:59,559 --> 00:09:00,320
a hundred thousand,

109
00:09:00,840 --> 00:09:01,679
a few hundred thousand,

110
00:09:02,639 --> 00:09:04,320
they can all cause a huge uproar,

111
00:09:04,879 --> 00:09:06,480
making people

112
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,440
show their dark side.

113
00:09:09,879 --> 00:09:11,000
What do you think 30 million

114
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:11,919
would do?

115
00:09:16,240 --> 00:09:18,000
We didn't spend a single cent
of that money.

116
00:09:18,200 --> 00:09:19,080
We have no fear.

117
00:09:21,559 --> 00:09:22,320
You dare not spend it?

118
00:09:23,080 --> 00:09:24,039
Just stare at that much cash

119
00:09:24,759 --> 00:09:25,639
every day?

120
00:09:26,240 --> 00:09:27,080
Doesn't it drive you crazy?

121
00:09:27,679 --> 00:09:28,320
No.

122
00:09:34,720 --> 00:09:35,960
So you've decided you won't

123
00:09:35,960 --> 00:09:36,559
give it back,

124
00:09:36,559 --> 00:09:37,000
right?

125
00:09:40,200 --> 00:09:40,559
Fine.

126
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:42,720
Is there no room for negotiation?

127
00:09:43,840 --> 00:09:44,320
No.

128
00:09:46,600 --> 00:09:47,360
I see.

129
00:10:00,480 --> 00:10:00,720
She...

130
00:10:01,519 --> 00:10:02,559
Did she leave?

131
00:10:03,600 --> 00:10:04,399
She went to the bathroom.

132
00:10:06,480 --> 00:10:07,000
It can't be.

133
00:10:07,759 --> 00:10:08,960
There is a bathroom right here.

134
00:10:14,159 --> 00:10:14,720
Jiang,

135
00:10:15,519 --> 00:10:16,639
do you have kids?

136
00:10:16,799 --> 00:10:18,000
A boy or a girl?

137
00:10:18,639 --> 00:10:20,360
Yes. A girl.

138
00:10:20,519 --> 00:10:21,840
She's already twelve.

139
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:24,440
Look.

140
00:10:25,279 --> 00:10:26,120
Her name is Yao.

141
00:10:26,840 --> 00:10:28,519
Such a sweet child.

142
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,080
Same age as Wenwen.

143
00:10:31,000 --> 00:10:31,960
Where is her school?

144
00:10:32,960 --> 00:10:33,960
It's in town.

145
00:10:34,480 --> 00:10:35,679
She is with her dad now.

146
00:10:36,080 --> 00:10:37,879
We haven't seen each other
for many years.

147
00:10:38,679 --> 00:10:39,600
Why?

148
00:10:39,759 --> 00:10:40,919
A child is part of

149
00:10:40,919 --> 00:10:42,080
her mother

150
00:10:42,879 --> 00:10:44,480
How could the bond be broken?

151
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,200
You don't know

152
00:10:46,200 --> 00:10:47,600
her dad's temper.

153
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:48,559
He drinks.

154
00:10:49,399 --> 00:10:50,279
Once he gets drunk, he beats me.

155
00:10:51,039 --> 00:10:52,159
Call the police.

156
00:10:53,120 --> 00:10:54,519
It's no use even begging him.

157
00:10:54,720 --> 00:10:56,360
Then you definitely should
call the police.

158
00:10:58,919 --> 00:11:01,080
My husband is just a thug.

159
00:11:01,360 --> 00:11:02,639
After I gave birth to my daughter,

160
00:11:02,799 --> 00:11:04,519
he went out fooling around every day.

161
00:11:04,879 --> 00:11:05,600
Later,

162
00:11:06,279 --> 00:11:08,399
he just vanished.

163
00:11:09,000 --> 00:11:10,279
He comes back once in a while,

164
00:11:10,559 --> 00:11:12,480
either asking for money or stealing it.

165
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:15,440
It's been three years

166
00:11:15,519 --> 00:11:16,559
since his last visit.

167
00:11:17,279 --> 00:11:18,200
So,

168
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:19,000
Tong is also

169
00:11:19,000 --> 00:11:19,960
a poor girl.

170
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:22,679
She's been living in fear
since childhood.

171
00:11:22,960 --> 00:11:25,279
When she was little,
I always thought,

172
00:11:25,279 --> 00:11:27,159
when she grows up,
find her a good husband.

173
00:11:27,360 --> 00:11:29,440
Someone who would look after her
like a father.

174
00:11:29,600 --> 00:11:30,799
I thought that would fix it.

175
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:32,480
I never expected

176
00:11:32,799 --> 00:11:33,960
she'd marry Yu Ming,

177
00:11:33,960 --> 00:11:35,240
that good-for-nothing.

178
00:11:35,320 --> 00:11:36,840
She not only suffered a lot...

179
00:11:37,399 --> 00:11:37,799
Fan Meijuan!

180
00:11:37,799 --> 00:11:38,840
He wouldn't even let us have a child.

181
00:11:39,759 --> 00:11:40,720
Where are Yu Ming

182
00:11:40,759 --> 00:11:42,440
and Wen Yitong on earth?

183
00:11:42,440 --> 00:11:44,440
Toad kisses frog,

184
00:11:44,440 --> 00:11:45,639
ugly mug, wild hug.

185
00:11:45,679 --> 00:11:46,519
Using a smokescreen,

186
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:47,960
he scams our kid

187
00:11:47,960 --> 00:11:49,639
out of tens of thousands on meals.

188
00:11:49,639 --> 00:11:50,200
What are you doing?

189
00:11:50,440 --> 00:11:51,600
Are you going to start a fight?

190
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:52,759
Your son already made a scene.

191
00:11:52,759 --> 00:11:53,919
Now it's you two.

192
00:11:54,080 --> 00:11:54,879
Let me tell you,

193
00:11:55,120 --> 00:11:56,120
she is a patient.

194
00:11:56,240 --> 00:11:57,759
She's in bad shape.

195
00:11:57,759 --> 00:11:58,879
So don't even think about it.

196
00:11:58,919 --> 00:12:00,279
You step aside!

197
00:12:00,759 --> 00:12:01,320
What are you doing?

198
00:12:01,759 --> 00:12:02,399
Fan Meijuan,

199
00:12:02,440 --> 00:12:03,919
where are you keeping your money?

200
00:12:04,039 --> 00:12:04,960
Now pay back.

201
00:12:05,039 --> 00:12:06,840
Those two even turned off their phones.

202
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,120
Are you asking her for money back

203
00:12:08,120 --> 00:12:09,120
or robbing her?

204
00:12:09,159 --> 00:12:10,080
At your age,

205
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,480
I see you're just small-time crooks.

206
00:12:11,879 --> 00:12:12,759
I'm calling the police.

207
00:12:12,759 --> 00:12:14,080
You're nothing but a bully.

208
00:12:14,279 --> 00:12:14,879
A wretch!

209
00:12:14,919 --> 00:12:15,919
A scammer!

210
00:12:16,200 --> 00:12:16,879
Ming

211
00:12:17,200 --> 00:12:18,200
thinks

212
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,759
he looks just like the guy

213
00:12:19,759 --> 00:12:20,799
who has won the lottery,

214
00:12:20,799 --> 00:12:22,320
so he went wild outside,

215
00:12:22,360 --> 00:12:23,559
putting on airs in every way.

216
00:12:24,120 --> 00:12:25,879
Who said we won the lottery?

217
00:12:26,080 --> 00:12:27,799
That was all you.

218
00:12:28,360 --> 00:12:28,919
Exactly.

219
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:29,919
What does them two

220
00:12:29,919 --> 00:12:30,840
winning the lottery

221
00:12:30,840 --> 00:12:32,039
have to do with you guys?

222
00:12:32,159 --> 00:12:32,879
When you thought

223
00:12:32,879 --> 00:12:34,039
they had won the lottery,

224
00:12:34,120 --> 00:12:35,360
you were ready to lick their boots.

225
00:12:35,440 --> 00:12:36,080
Now that

226
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:37,720
you know they didn't win,

227
00:12:37,919 --> 00:12:39,360
and you're jumping out

228
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,440
blaming them like crazy.

229
00:12:40,519 --> 00:12:41,879
Are you even human?

230
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:42,279
You...

231
00:12:42,399 --> 00:12:43,320
What about me?

232
00:12:44,360 --> 00:12:46,000
I can't talk with you.

233
00:12:46,000 --> 00:12:47,320
Talk, talk, talk about what?

234
00:12:47,320 --> 00:12:49,080
If you've got nothing to say,
then shut up.

235
00:12:49,080 --> 00:12:49,879
Why don't you

236
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:50,639
get lost?

237
00:12:51,360 --> 00:12:52,120
Who's getting lost?

238
00:12:52,320 --> 00:12:53,200
Roll yourself!

239
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:53,840
Just you wait.

240
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:55,360
I tell you,

241
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:57,799
you just tell Ming and Yitong

242
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:58,759
I'm not done

243
00:12:58,759 --> 00:12:59,879
with them

244
00:13:00,039 --> 00:13:01,519
about this.

245
00:13:01,960 --> 00:13:02,759
Darling, let's go.

246
00:13:03,360 --> 00:13:03,720
Go!

247
00:13:03,879 --> 00:13:04,559
Money!

248
00:13:04,840 --> 00:13:05,679
Let's go.

249
00:13:05,879 --> 00:13:06,559
See you.

250
00:13:07,120 --> 00:13:08,080
See you no more.

251
00:13:12,639 --> 00:13:13,840
What kind of people are they?

252
00:13:15,039 --> 00:13:15,960
Are you okay?

253
00:13:17,120 --> 00:13:18,879
You look so soft and gentle,

254
00:13:19,159 --> 00:13:20,279
but you've got some fire in you.

255
00:13:22,130 --> 00:13:24,430
(Zhan)

256
00:13:25,720 --> 00:13:26,159
Ma'am,

257
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,600
I'll take a call.

258
00:13:27,759 --> 00:13:28,240
Sure.

259
00:13:31,960 --> 00:13:33,240
I thought we said no more calls?

260
00:13:33,399 --> 00:13:34,679
Texting doesn't make noise.

261
00:13:34,919 --> 00:13:36,000
Check your phone. You'll see.

262
00:13:36,679 --> 00:13:37,360
How is it going?

263
00:13:44,720 --> 00:13:45,320
Not bad.

264
00:13:45,639 --> 00:13:46,279
She trusts me.

265
00:13:47,159 --> 00:13:48,240
It's not enough.

266
00:13:48,519 --> 00:13:49,519
Her daughter and son-in-law

267
00:13:49,519 --> 00:13:50,480
also have to trust you.

268
00:13:51,759 --> 00:13:52,679
You worry too much.

269
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:53,840
I know it.

270
00:14:01,200 --> 00:14:02,759
Wenwen taught me how to

271
00:14:02,759 --> 00:14:03,559
buy fruits online.

272
00:14:03,919 --> 00:14:06,039
I ordered some Pujiang oranges for you.

273
00:14:06,080 --> 00:14:07,320
You are from Pujiang.

274
00:14:07,399 --> 00:14:08,279
I heard

275
00:14:08,440 --> 00:14:09,440
when you eat these,

276
00:14:09,519 --> 00:14:11,919
the sweetness lingers from the mouth
all the way down to the stomach.

277
00:14:12,519 --> 00:14:13,600
I've learned to place an order.

278
00:14:16,000 --> 00:14:16,440
Good.

279
00:14:29,519 --> 00:14:31,279
I can't do it.

280
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,159
Wait, you tell me,

281
00:14:35,159 --> 00:14:36,240
why can't you do it?

282
00:14:37,639 --> 00:14:38,000
Well,

283
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,440
isn't it very easy

284
00:14:39,440 --> 00:14:40,480
for your department

285
00:14:40,480 --> 00:14:41,399
to freeze a credit card?

286
00:14:41,879 --> 00:14:44,759
Either the card hasn't been used
for a long time,

287
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:47,120
or the payments are overdue,

288
00:14:47,480 --> 00:14:49,279
or risky transactions.

289
00:14:49,720 --> 00:14:50,399
That card

290
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:52,039
was activated in less than a month.

291
00:14:52,559 --> 00:14:54,159
It doesn't meet any of those

292
00:14:54,200 --> 00:14:55,080
three conditions.

293
00:14:55,480 --> 00:14:56,360
Are you trying

294
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,279
to mess with me?

295
00:14:59,120 --> 00:15:01,600
♪BBQ, spicy, crayfish♪

296
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:03,639
♪Kisses, kisses♪

297
00:15:07,279 --> 00:15:08,000
That cocky look.

298
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,320
You're really pushing your luck.

299
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:12,039
Just don't ask

300
00:15:12,039 --> 00:15:13,200
anything from me in the future.

301
00:15:14,600 --> 00:15:15,759
Darned brat.

302
00:15:16,679 --> 00:15:17,559
Morning, Mr. President.

303
00:15:23,799 --> 00:15:24,840
I'll make an announcement.

304
00:15:25,639 --> 00:15:26,639
Starting today,

305
00:15:27,000 --> 00:15:28,960
Li Yunliang will serve as our bank's

306
00:15:29,399 --> 00:15:30,480
Deputy President for Business.

307
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,320
The personnel meeting

308
00:15:32,600 --> 00:15:33,519
will be held this afternoon.

309
00:15:33,879 --> 00:15:34,320
Mr. Li,

310
00:15:35,279 --> 00:15:36,039
say a few words?

311
00:15:36,399 --> 00:15:36,720
Sure.

312
00:15:37,039 --> 00:15:38,200
Thank you for all your trust.

313
00:15:38,480 --> 00:15:40,080
Thank you for all your support.

314
00:15:40,159 --> 00:15:40,960
Thank you all

315
00:15:40,960 --> 00:15:42,159
for giving me this platform,

316
00:15:42,279 --> 00:15:43,440
the opportunity

317
00:15:43,480 --> 00:15:44,440
to serve everyone,

318
00:15:44,600 --> 00:15:45,600
and contribute to our bank.

319
00:15:45,639 --> 00:15:46,759
I will take today

320
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:48,879
as a new starting point in my life.

321
00:15:49,080 --> 00:15:50,000
With a fresh mindset,

322
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:51,440
I will quickly adapt to my new role.

323
00:15:51,639 --> 00:15:52,720
I'll repay your trust

324
00:15:52,960 --> 00:15:54,840
and expectations

325
00:15:54,840 --> 00:15:56,039
with strong performance.

326
00:15:56,279 --> 00:15:56,799
Thank you.

327
00:15:57,080 --> 00:15:58,440
Bravo!

328
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:02,240
Some nobody like you
gets to be a deputy president?

329
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:04,440
That should've been mine.

330
00:16:08,159 --> 00:16:09,039
What a dumb rule.

331
00:16:11,519 --> 00:16:12,000
Qian.

332
00:16:15,279 --> 00:16:15,679
Tell me

333
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:17,320
what's the rule.

334
00:16:18,639 --> 00:16:19,000
Mr. Qian,

335
00:16:19,240 --> 00:16:20,840
my father-in-law is having surgery
that day.

336
00:16:21,159 --> 00:16:22,399
Could you swap shifts with me?

337
00:16:22,720 --> 00:16:23,440
Please.

338
00:16:29,279 --> 00:16:29,840
I can't.

339
00:16:30,600 --> 00:16:31,200
Jie.

340
00:16:31,759 --> 00:16:32,759
Last time you wouldn't swap.

341
00:16:32,799 --> 00:16:34,440
My wife fought me for two days.

342
00:16:35,159 --> 00:16:36,240
Besides, I've swapped for you

343
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:36,840
before.

344
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:43,279
I can't.

345
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:50,519
I make the rules.

346
00:16:51,039 --> 00:16:53,120
♪BBQ, spicy crayfish♪

347
00:16:53,320 --> 00:16:55,080
♪Kisses, kisses♪

348
00:17:08,400 --> 00:17:09,160
This mother

349
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:10,039
looks intimidating.

350
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,400
Her gaze

351
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:13,319
dripped with superiority.

352
00:17:14,279 --> 00:17:16,119
My calves haven't stopped shaking.

353
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:18,119
There's always a bigger fish.

354
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:18,960
That kind of ambush.

355
00:17:19,160 --> 00:17:20,119
Is she still a fish?

356
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,039
Could a fish eat a person?

357
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:25,039
Hong Jinkui is all bark but no bite.

358
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:26,079
She is not like that.

359
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:28,039
Chen Zinuo

360
00:17:28,039 --> 00:17:30,200
must have told her mom about the money.

361
00:17:30,759 --> 00:17:32,039
Double-faced.

362
00:17:32,039 --> 00:17:33,519
She kept saying
she didn't want that money.

363
00:17:33,599 --> 00:17:34,200
So sly.

364
00:17:34,279 --> 00:17:35,559
She is just so sly.

365
00:17:35,640 --> 00:17:36,559
She waited for her mother

366
00:17:36,559 --> 00:17:38,160
to get out
so they could come after us together.

367
00:17:38,319 --> 00:17:39,000
I think we should

368
00:17:39,000 --> 00:17:39,799
call Ouyang right away

369
00:17:39,799 --> 00:17:40,440
and remind him

370
00:17:40,559 --> 00:17:41,720
not to be tricked by her like us.

371
00:17:41,920 --> 00:17:43,119
Don't let her mislead him.

372
00:17:43,839 --> 00:17:44,440
It won't happen.

373
00:17:59,279 --> 00:18:00,039
Jiang.

374
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:04,680
Jiang.

375
00:18:33,359 --> 00:18:34,000
Sorry.

376
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,759
The number you dialed

377
00:18:35,759 --> 00:18:37,039
can't be reached now.

378
00:18:38,039 --> 00:18:39,480
Why can't I get through?

379
00:18:41,079 --> 00:18:42,240
What's going on?

380
00:18:49,319 --> 00:18:49,839
Hello, mom.

381
00:18:50,279 --> 00:18:52,440
Tong, I just woke up

382
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,119
and I haven't seen Jiang.

383
00:18:54,119 --> 00:18:55,559
I just don't see her now.

384
00:18:55,599 --> 00:18:57,799
The food on the table is all cold.

385
00:18:57,799 --> 00:18:59,680
She's been gone for a long time.

386
00:18:59,920 --> 00:19:02,000
I tried calling her,
but her phone's off.

387
00:19:02,279 --> 00:19:03,920
Could something have happened to her?

388
00:19:04,599 --> 00:19:06,079
Maybe her phone is dead.

389
00:19:06,319 --> 00:19:08,279
I've been asleep for hours.

390
00:19:09,039 --> 00:19:10,759
Something doesn't feel right.

391
00:19:10,799 --> 00:19:12,680
My eyelid keeps twitching.

392
00:19:12,839 --> 00:19:13,599
Don't be anxious.

393
00:19:13,680 --> 00:19:14,440
I'm coming back.

394
00:19:14,480 --> 00:19:15,119
Be right there.

395
00:19:16,519 --> 00:19:17,319
Drop me off up ahead.

396
00:19:17,359 --> 00:19:17,960
I need to go home.

397
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:18,880
What happened?

398
00:19:19,039 --> 00:19:20,519
Jiang Juan is missing.

399
00:19:20,720 --> 00:19:21,599
Mom's home alone.

400
00:19:21,599 --> 00:19:22,559
I'll go check on her.

401
00:19:22,839 --> 00:19:23,680
You go find Ouyang.

402
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,400
Any news about Yao?

403
00:19:30,920 --> 00:19:31,720
It's hard to

404
00:19:32,519 --> 00:19:33,440
track migrant populations.

405
00:19:39,960 --> 00:19:41,759
Tell your hometown contact
to put in some effort.

406
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:42,960
If he can find her,

407
00:19:43,119 --> 00:19:44,279
we won't shortchange him.

408
00:19:48,319 --> 00:19:48,960
Does it look good?

409
00:19:55,119 --> 00:19:55,960
I told Fan Meijuan

410
00:19:56,000 --> 00:19:57,440
she looked good in that red dress.

411
00:19:58,319 --> 00:19:58,960
I didn't expect

412
00:20:00,079 --> 00:20:01,400
she bought me one too.

413
00:20:04,960 --> 00:20:06,920
The fabric of this dress is so good.

414
00:20:07,759 --> 00:20:09,079
So smooth to the touch.

415
00:20:17,119 --> 00:20:17,799
I thought

416
00:20:17,799 --> 00:20:18,559
she's very stingy?

417
00:20:24,119 --> 00:20:25,079
This dress wasn't cheap?

418
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:28,079
You fool.

419
00:20:29,839 --> 00:20:31,559
Do you know what this means?

420
00:20:32,319 --> 00:20:32,839
I don't know.

421
00:20:33,519 --> 00:20:34,039
What?

422
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:41,599
It means

423
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:43,640
she is starting to trust me.

424
00:20:45,880 --> 00:20:46,440
But

425
00:20:47,519 --> 00:20:49,000
trust only isn't enough.

426
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:53,759
What are you doing?

427
00:20:54,119 --> 00:20:54,839
Are you crazy?

428
00:21:00,759 --> 00:21:02,359
I need her to sympathize with me.

429
00:21:04,079 --> 00:21:04,960
I need her to feel

430
00:21:06,160 --> 00:21:08,119
like we're in the same boat.

431
00:21:09,160 --> 00:21:11,200
That's how hearts get closer.

432
00:21:13,119 --> 00:21:14,079
And when hearts are close,

433
00:21:16,319 --> 00:21:18,680
our chances get much better.

434
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:24,400
Who is it?

435
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:25,079
It's me.

436
00:21:28,119 --> 00:21:29,000
You were right.

437
00:21:29,559 --> 00:21:31,480
That 30 million is really a hot potato.

438
00:21:31,480 --> 00:21:32,039
Very hot.

439
00:21:32,160 --> 00:21:33,279
Such a headache.

440
00:21:34,400 --> 00:21:34,960
First,

441
00:21:35,559 --> 00:21:36,880
someone climbed through my window

442
00:21:36,960 --> 00:21:37,519
at night.

443
00:21:38,400 --> 00:21:39,079
Then,

444
00:21:39,519 --> 00:21:41,279
someone started following me.

445
00:21:41,799 --> 00:21:44,519
And finally, someone dug a tunnel.

446
00:21:44,640 --> 00:21:46,279
Three workers. Digging.

447
00:21:46,359 --> 00:21:47,200
Dug and dug,

448
00:21:47,200 --> 00:21:48,119
and they broke through.

449
00:21:48,119 --> 00:21:49,480
I caught them and scared one of them

450
00:21:49,480 --> 00:21:50,319
half to death.

451
00:21:50,359 --> 00:21:51,480
I even had to compensate them.

452
00:21:51,559 --> 00:21:52,839
Now it's that Li Jin.

453
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:54,039
She got out of prison.

454
00:21:54,079 --> 00:21:54,960
You know Li Jin, right?

455
00:21:56,240 --> 00:21:56,920
After she got out,

456
00:21:57,079 --> 00:21:58,240
I found it really strange.

457
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,240
How did she know I had the money?

458
00:22:00,319 --> 00:22:00,880
Only a few of us

459
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:01,960
know about the money, right?

460
00:22:03,000 --> 00:22:03,680
No one else.

461
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:05,279
It must be Chen Zinuo then.

462
00:22:05,759 --> 00:22:07,240
Li Jin just looks sinister.

463
00:22:07,480 --> 00:22:09,359
Sitting there drinking coffee,
demanding money.

464
00:22:09,559 --> 00:22:10,599
Just casually asking.

465
00:22:10,680 --> 00:22:12,519
Chen Zinuo doesn't look

466
00:22:12,519 --> 00:22:13,640
like her mother very much,

467
00:22:13,720 --> 00:22:15,279
but she shares her mother's mind,

468
00:22:15,319 --> 00:22:17,119
the sinister kind.

469
00:22:24,839 --> 00:22:26,000
The person who just walked by,

470
00:22:26,279 --> 00:22:26,839
was that her?

471
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:29,880
What's she doing here?

472
00:22:30,200 --> 00:22:31,559
She lives here. What's wrong?

473
00:22:31,599 --> 00:22:33,359
Her mother just got out

474
00:22:33,359 --> 00:22:34,160
of prison.

475
00:22:34,240 --> 00:22:34,799
So she

476
00:22:34,960 --> 00:22:36,160
shouldn't be living here, right?

477
00:22:36,319 --> 00:22:36,759
Why not?

478
00:22:37,559 --> 00:22:38,440
That has nothing

479
00:22:38,440 --> 00:22:39,000
to do with

480
00:22:39,000 --> 00:22:39,559
where she lives?

481
00:22:41,680 --> 00:22:42,480
No more words.

482
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:43,480
Seeing is believing.

483
00:22:43,480 --> 00:22:44,119
Come with me.

484
00:23:19,839 --> 00:23:20,720
How much is this?

485
00:23:21,480 --> 00:23:22,440
60 million.

486
00:23:24,920 --> 00:23:25,880
I thought it was thirty.

487
00:23:26,039 --> 00:23:27,400
It was.

488
00:23:27,640 --> 00:23:29,200
Now there's another thirty.

489
00:23:29,279 --> 00:23:30,400
It's 60 million in total now.

490
00:23:30,799 --> 00:23:32,119
Another 30 million?

491
00:23:36,559 --> 00:23:37,359
This board at the back

492
00:23:37,559 --> 00:23:38,839
can help support your waist.

493
00:23:40,720 --> 00:23:41,559
I have to say,

494
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:43,599
this stuff is truly useful.

495
00:23:44,039 --> 00:23:44,880
Feels pretty good.

496
00:23:44,960 --> 00:23:45,640
It's so good.

497
00:23:45,839 --> 00:23:47,200
Thank you. Please, sit down.

498
00:23:47,240 --> 00:23:48,640
Resting is better than anything else.

499
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:50,640
Let me get you some oranges.

500
00:23:50,839 --> 00:23:51,799
No need.

501
00:23:52,039 --> 00:23:52,799
I just came to see you.

502
00:23:52,799 --> 00:23:54,720
It really is comfortable. Jiajia,

503
00:23:54,720 --> 00:23:55,920
you're so clever.

504
00:23:56,799 --> 00:23:58,119
My mom feels awful if she doesn't move.

505
00:23:59,160 --> 00:23:59,559
Sit.

506
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:02,880
You called me over.

507
00:24:03,440 --> 00:24:04,079
What did you

508
00:24:04,480 --> 00:24:05,480
want to tell me?

509
00:24:07,839 --> 00:24:08,359
Look.

510
00:24:10,039 --> 00:24:10,839
We didn't win

511
00:24:12,559 --> 00:24:13,160
the lottery.

512
00:24:16,920 --> 00:24:17,920
No 130 million?

513
00:24:18,599 --> 00:24:19,039
No.

514
00:24:20,279 --> 00:24:22,079
That's good. It's a good thing.

515
00:24:22,359 --> 00:24:23,039
It's a good thing.

516
00:24:23,640 --> 00:24:24,599
I finally told you the truth.

517
00:24:26,400 --> 00:24:27,240
Apart from this,

518
00:24:27,759 --> 00:24:29,000
what else do you want to say to me?

519
00:24:30,279 --> 00:24:30,960
Yu Ming and I...

520
00:24:31,640 --> 00:24:32,160
Jiajia,

521
00:24:32,839 --> 00:24:34,119
these are Pujiang oranges.

522
00:24:34,160 --> 00:24:35,359
Come on, have some.

523
00:24:35,400 --> 00:24:36,079
Thank you.

524
00:24:36,279 --> 00:24:37,799
Take a break. Have a seat.

525
00:24:37,799 --> 00:24:38,680
Come on, sit down.

526
00:24:40,799 --> 00:24:42,279
Just don't move around so much.

527
00:24:42,359 --> 00:24:43,759
Get more rest.

528
00:24:43,920 --> 00:24:44,440
Yes, more rest.

529
00:24:44,440 --> 00:24:45,640
This thing is really good.

530
00:24:45,720 --> 00:24:46,799
Come on, have some.

531
00:24:46,799 --> 00:24:47,880
I've got some. Help yourself.

532
00:24:49,079 --> 00:24:49,759
Give you.

533
00:24:52,759 --> 00:24:53,359
Calling all day.

534
00:24:53,440 --> 00:24:54,039
Sorry.

535
00:24:56,319 --> 00:24:58,160
Why can't I get through?

536
00:24:58,279 --> 00:24:59,400
She must be busy.

537
00:24:59,400 --> 00:25:01,359
She'll call back when she sees it.

538
00:25:01,920 --> 00:25:03,440
That day, she stood up for me

539
00:25:03,440 --> 00:25:04,440
against Yu Ming's relatives.

540
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,039
I'm afraid she might get bullied.

541
00:25:08,240 --> 00:25:09,319
I can't just sit here.

542
00:25:09,759 --> 00:25:10,480
Wait, don't...

543
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:12,640
Don't move.

544
00:25:12,640 --> 00:25:13,240
I'll go.

545
00:25:22,359 --> 00:25:23,240
Oh, my god!

546
00:25:23,839 --> 00:25:25,480
What happened to you?

547
00:25:27,279 --> 00:25:28,519
Did your husband come find you?

548
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:29,640
Did he beat you again?

549
00:25:29,680 --> 00:25:30,680
No.

550
00:25:31,279 --> 00:25:32,279
I fell.

551
00:25:33,319 --> 00:25:34,920
I fell down a slope,

552
00:25:34,960 --> 00:25:35,640
and I passed out.

553
00:25:36,000 --> 00:25:36,839
In a daze,

554
00:25:37,079 --> 00:25:38,240
I woke up and came back.

555
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,119
He did hit you.

556
00:25:39,440 --> 00:25:39,960
This won't do.

557
00:25:40,480 --> 00:25:41,039
Call the police!

558
00:25:42,559 --> 00:25:43,640
It's fine.

559
00:25:45,839 --> 00:25:46,680
It's time to cook.

560
00:25:47,839 --> 00:25:49,920
Let me wash up. I'll get to it.

561
00:25:52,079 --> 00:25:52,599
Wait.

562
00:25:52,640 --> 00:25:54,039
Your wound should be addressed.

563
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:56,279
How can you cook?

564
00:25:56,279 --> 00:25:57,400
It's fine.

565
00:26:02,519 --> 00:26:03,559
Call the police.

566
00:26:05,480 --> 00:26:06,279
No.

567
00:26:07,599 --> 00:26:08,119
Ming,

568
00:26:09,640 --> 00:26:10,559
can you listen to me for once?

569
00:26:11,519 --> 00:26:12,599
Now things have

570
00:26:12,720 --> 00:26:13,799
gotten out of control.

571
00:26:13,799 --> 00:26:14,319
You know that.

572
00:26:14,599 --> 00:26:15,839
You're not still excited, are you?

573
00:26:16,000 --> 00:26:16,759
With that much cash,

574
00:26:16,759 --> 00:26:17,880
I was terrified.

575
00:26:18,400 --> 00:26:19,079
Me too.

576
00:26:19,720 --> 00:26:20,640
Maybe now I...

577
00:26:20,880 --> 00:26:21,519
I...

578
00:26:21,920 --> 00:26:22,880
My actions

579
00:26:22,880 --> 00:26:24,160
might already be a crime.

580
00:26:24,359 --> 00:26:24,960
What crime?

581
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:26,000
You spent the money?

582
00:26:26,599 --> 00:26:27,279
Yes.

583
00:26:28,640 --> 00:26:29,599
No, I...

584
00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:32,400
I haven't spent a cent of it.

585
00:26:33,039 --> 00:26:33,880
This whole thing.

586
00:26:34,160 --> 00:26:35,759
The longer we drag it out,
the worse it gets.

587
00:26:35,759 --> 00:26:36,279
Don't you see?

588
00:26:36,440 --> 00:26:37,880
If Chen Zinuo's mother gets involved,

589
